#summary This is the cost per element in major data structures offered by Java and Guava. It is generated by [http://code.google.com/p/memory-measurer/source/browse/trunk/test/memorymeasurer/ElementCostOfDataStructures.java ElementCostOfDataStructures.java].
#labels Featured

= Introduction =

Ever wondered what's the cost of adding an entry to a HashMap? Or a new element in a TreeSet? No more head-scratching, you can consult the following list and know very precisely the cost per elements in your data structures (using their default settings when not specified).
